    <p style="color:var(--text2);font-size:14px;line-height:1.75;">Package management is infrastructure. Senior engineers know that <strong style="color:var(--text);">every package install is a trust decision</strong> — you're running arbitrary root-level scripts from whoever maintains that package. They hold production package versions deliberately and upgrade on a schedule. They know the difference between the apt metadata cache (<code>/var/lib/apt/lists/</code>) and the download cache (<code>/var/cache/apt/archives/</code>) and can clean them independently. In automation they always use <code>apt-get</code> for predictable output, always combine <code>update + install + clean</code> in one Docker RUN layer, and always check <code>apt list --upgradable</code> before deciding whether to upgrade — never blindly.</p>
